The idea is that plugins can register hooks that can be invoked by other plugins. For example, the markdown-it plugin could register this hook internally:

```js
site.hooks.addMarkdownItPlugin = (plugin, options) => {
  markdown.use(plugin, options);
};
```

So the toc plugin could invoke this hook:

```js
export default function toc() {
  return (site) => {
    site.hooks.addMarkdownItPlugin(plugin, options);
  }
}
```

Other use cases: postcss, remark, etc.

